sentences: Born in Naples on 5 April 1883, Della Corte studied law at the University of the native city, but was self-taught in music.
In Turin, Della Corte also taught history of music, both at the Conservatory (1926–53) and at the University (1939–53).

After some short experiences in Neapolitan papers (initially at the Don Marzio, then at Il Mattino), he moved to Turin, where he was music critic  for La Stampa from 1919 to May 1967.
His main interests were the comic opera of the 18th century, Gluck and Verdi.
